choices.text: morally acceptable Author: Cape Verdeans are religious and the country is a former Portuguese colony, but abortion is either legal or tolerated in Most African countries including Mozambique, Namibia, Tanzania, South Africa and Ugandais illegal, but almost half of American and European countries allow terminations. About one in six pregnancy terminations happen illegally or “on the black market,” with the rest done legally in U.S. and Western Europe In many cases the majority of African countries forbid termination of pregnancies unless the pregnancy was the result of incest, rape, foetal abnormality or danger to the life of the mother.
